DNStt Tunnel
=============

This project was inspired by masterking32/MasterDnsVPN.

https://github.com/masterking32/MasterDnsVPN

The original implementation is written in Python. I am not a big fan of Python
for networking tools like this, so I decided to port the idea to Go while also
making some structural changes to the design.

One of the main changes is the removal of the session system used in the
original project. In environments where there is a single bridge server
(commonly the case in Iran), maintaining global sessions can introduce
unnecessary complexity and bottlenecks.

Instead, this implementation focuses on a simpler server-side model.

For every incoming SOCKS5 connection:

1. The client requests a new stream ID from the server
2. The TCP stream is split into smaller chunks
3. Each chunk is transmitted through the tunnel
4. Packets are tagged with the stream ID and packet ID

The transport layer uses a DNS-style tunnel based on DNStt techniques.

Status
------

This project is still under development.

The implementation is experimental and many things may change as the design
evolves.

Feedback
--------

If you have suggestions or improvements, feel free to share them.

Constructive feedback is always welcome.

Thanks for taking the time to read this.